    <item>
      <title>P-Speed Jump/3rd Jump Tier</title>
      <author>TotalStache</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/556611</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/556611#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">d7788a120b4f3a707d9e8c0602e855aa95174958</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 18 Nov 2024 01:37:37 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/673a98010a9ff.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/673a987964313.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;In Super Mario Bros. 3 and Super Mario World, when you're moving/walking, you could jump 5 blocks high, and at max speed, you could jump 6 blocks high, but in Wonder, even if you're running at max speed, you'll jump 5 blocks, so there is no jump height difference when walking or running at max speed. But with this mod, you can now get that extra block of height when at max speed, and this doesn't affect any of the other standard jump heights, so standstill/spin jump will still be 4 blocks, and walking/moving will still be 5 blocks. This mod works with the floaty high jump badge as well, so the max running speed jump is 7 blocks for this badge. The crouch jump badge charge-up timer has been slightly reduced, and the timed high jump badge can now go one block higher (7 blocks) to compensate for the base moveset having a buff. Enemy bounces have been made one block higher as well, just like the old games (6 blocks and 7 blocks for the floaty jump badge).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod works on all characters.</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/p-speedjump_092b1.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Other/Misc</category>
      <category>Other/Misc</category>
    </item>
